One of the governorship aspirants, on the platform of the All Progressives Congress, APC, in Ekiti State, Hon. Femi Bamisile has said that he will not defect to another political party based on the outcome of the last primary election of the party. Bamisile, who is a member of the House of Representatives, gave the assurance while speaking with newsmen in Ado-Ekiti. The lawmaker also said that he will not engage in any action that will be detrimental to the party and Ekiti people in general, pointing out that after due consultations with some of his legal team, he had to rescind certain decisions for the party to move forward. The former gubernatorial aspirant posited that he equally consulted widely with members of his constituency, his family, friends and political associates before deciding to back out of certain actions that might not be positive for the party.